00:21:10,627 --> 00:21:15,433
This is our first movie together,
our first lead role film.

382
00:21:15,482 --> 00:21:17,401
We were super nervous.

383
00:21:17,426 --> 00:21:19,962
And when the first teaser came out,

384
00:21:19,987 --> 00:21:25,325
I really felt how high
people’s expectations were.

385
00:21:25,492 --> 00:21:27,494
Reading those reactions,

386
00:21:27,519 --> 00:21:30,480
that’s when I started
to feel the pressure

387
00:21:30,514 --> 00:21:33,350
but I tried to
shake it off quickly.

388
00:21:33,375 --> 00:21:36,952
Because when I work under pressure,

389
00:21:37,421 --> 00:21:39,589
it doesn’t really work for me.

390
00:21:39,614 --> 00:21:41,300
I find it harder to function.

391
00:21:41,447 --> 00:21:45,095
I prefer working while having fun

392
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:47,706
not thinking too much
about what people expect.

393
00:21:47,764 --> 00:21:51,184
And it helped that we
were given a workshop.

394
00:21:51,209 --> 00:21:52,994
Once we started shooting,

395
00:21:53,019 --> 00:21:56,729
I was reminded to just feel whatever
the character is feeling

396
00:21:56,815 --> 00:21:59,359
to be in the moment.

397
00:21:59,384 --> 00:22:03,347
Instead of calculating
my next cues and actions.

398
00:22:03,431 --> 00:22:06,184
When I try to prove too much,
I end up doing less.

399
00:22:06,209 --> 00:22:08,336
So in the workshop,
I was reminded—

400
00:22:08,361 --> 00:22:10,446
I just need to feel every scene.

401
00:22:10,555 --> 00:22:11,805
From the very beginning,

402
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:13,290
we honestly couldn’t believe it

403
00:22:13,373 --> 00:22:17,269
that we actually have a film now.

404
00:22:17,294 --> 00:22:19,171
And for me, it’s always
been a dream of mine

405
00:22:19,171 --> 00:22:22,049
to eventually be on
the silver screen, really.

406
00:22:22,090 --> 00:22:23,810
and you know, this is it.

407
00:22:23,835 --> 00:22:26,945
I’m just also glad
that my partner is Ash.

408
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:29,681
We’ve already had the
chance to work together,

409
00:22:29,706 --> 00:22:31,879
and we’re really close now,

410
00:22:31,970 --> 00:22:33,160
and the bond we have,

411
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:35,729
the way we work together—
it really flows really well.

412
00:22:35,754 --> 00:22:38,957
which I think is the beauty of
Ang Mutya ng Section E as well.

413
00:22:38,982 --> 00:22:42,444
We are able to develop our connection
or our chemistry

414
00:22:42,569 --> 00:22:45,739
and now we get to show
that on the silver screen.

415
00:22:45,739 --> 00:22:47,199
I’m very thankful that Ashtine and Andres

416
00:22:47,199 --> 00:22:50,160
were the ones
cast in this project,

417
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:52,723
because they’re very easy to work with.

418
00:22:52,748 --> 00:22:56,683
They’re thinking actors,
they take direction well,

419
00:22:56,708 --> 00:22:58,126
They understand what’s needed.

420
00:22:58,335 --> 00:23:01,372
They’re not the kind of artists
who are just here for a quick gig.

421
00:23:01,459 --> 00:23:04,337
They really put their
hearts into this project—

422
00:23:04,362 --> 00:23:06,031
they even did their own workshops.

423
00:23:06,056 --> 00:23:12,107
On set, they help each other
bring the characters to life.

424
00:23:12,474 --> 00:23:17,491
Because of that, shooting the scenes
went really smoothly.

425
00:23:17,516 --> 00:23:22,850
Even the ones I thought would be tough
because they were heavy

426
00:23:22,883 --> 00:23:23,902
once we got there,

427
00:23:23,902 --> 00:23:26,613
I’m surprised. They already
had their lines memorized,

428
00:23:26,638 --> 00:23:28,423
they knew the approach

429
00:23:28,448 --> 00:23:31,618
I’m very thankful that they were
the ones who ended up in this project.

